## Part 3: Hysteresis Primitive Detail

The hysteresis gate prevents rapid oscillation between modes. Implementation:

```rust
pub struct HysteresisGate {
    /// Metric value above which the gate activates
    pub threshold_enter: f64,
    /// Metric value below which the gate deactivates
    pub threshold_exit: f64,
    /// Minimum time (ms) in current state before transition allowed
    pub min_hold_ms: u64,
    /// Current activation state
    pub active: bool,
    /// Timestamp (ms since epoch) of last state transition
    pub last_transition_ms: u64,
}

impl HysteresisGate {
    pub fn should_activate(&mut self, metric: f64, now_ms: u64) -> bool {
        let hold_elapsed = now_ms.saturating_sub(self.last_transition_ms) >= self.min_hold_ms;

        if !self.active && metric >= self.threshold_enter && hold_elapsed {
            self.active = true;
            self.last_transition_ms = now_ms;
        } else if self.active && metric <= self.threshold_exit && hold_elapsed {
            self.active = false;
            self.last_transition_ms = now_ms;
        }

        self.active
    }
}
```

Example: Error rate hysteresis
- `threshold_enter = 0.3` (activate when error rate > 30%)
- `threshold_exit = 0.1` (deactivate when error rate < 10%)
- `min_hold_ms = 10_000` (hold for at least 10 seconds)

This prevents the controller from flapping between Execute and Recover modes when the error rate hovers around the threshold.

---

## Part 4: Exact Arcan Integration Point

The most precise integration point is in `KernelRuntime::tick_on_branch()` at `/Users/broomva/broomva.tech/live/aiOS/crates/aios-runtime/src/lib.rs:243-582`.

The current flow is:
```
line 282: mode = self.estimate_mode(&state, pending_approvals.len());
line 284: append StateEstimated event
line 476: self.apply_homeostasis_controllers(&mut state, &report);
line 477: mode = self.estimate_mode(&state, 0);
```

With Autonomic, this becomes:
```
line 282: 
  // First, try to get Autonomic's gating profile
  let autonomic_profile = self.fetch_autonomic_gating(session_id).await;
  mode = if let Some(profile) = &autonomic_profile {
      // Use Autonomic's computed mode (derived from rules + hysteresis)
      profile.suggested_mode.unwrap_or_else(|| self.estimate_mode(&state, pending_approvals.len()))
  } else {
      self.estimate_mode(&state, pending_approvals.len())
  };
  // Apply economic gates from Autonomic profile
  if let Some(profile) = &autonomic_profile {
      // Store profile for use in tool gating later
      self.apply_economic_gates(&profile.economic);
  }
```

The `fetch_autonomic_gating()` method would be:
```rust
async fn fetch_autonomic_gating(&self, session_id: &SessionId) -> Option<AutonomicGatingProfile> {
    let url = self.config.autonomic_url.as_ref()?;
    let client = reqwest::Client::builder()
        .timeout(Duration::from_millis(500)) // Fast timeout -- advisory only
        .build()
        .ok()?;
    client
        .get(format!("{url}/gating/{}", session_id.as_str()))
        .send()
        .await
        .ok()?
        .json::<AutonomicGatingProfile>()
        .await
        .ok()
}
```

Key properties:
- 500ms timeout ensures Autonomic never blocks the agent loop
- Failure returns `None` -- Arcan falls back to its existing `estimate_mode()`
- The profile is advisory, not mandatory
- No architectural change to the kernel contract

